He stresses that it is important to check that there are bats before renovations are carried out because unconscious destruction of beds can destroy up to 400 females and cubs, and destroy the entire local population.
Bats are protected and it is illegal to kill, torture, or disturb or destroy their beds.
Elizabeth Ferel, a Scottish officer in the Bat Protection Trust, encourages the public to help.
